<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[137,776,1194,1315]" lastBlockId="12.[835,1474,189,341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[137,262,1194,1218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
— Body length: 
<quantity box="[475,584,1194,1218]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
. This species is very closely related with 
<taxonomicName authority="Freitag &amp; Jach. Colouration" authorityName="Freitag &amp; Jach. Colouration" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manguao">
<emphasis box="[432,654,1227,1250]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Hydraena manguao</emphasis>
Freitag &amp; Jäch. Colouration
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal punctation and body form agree very well with the latter (see Freitag &amp; Jäch, 2007: 
<figureCitation box="[732,864,189,1314]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[113,148,2063,2085]" captionTargetBox="[153,1421,173,2029]" captionTargetId="figure-8@11.[141,1429,173,2044]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 11. Hydraena paulmoritz: a, aedeagus in lateral view; b, aedeagus, dorsal view; aedeagus, ventral view; d, male sternite X and spiculum; e, gonocoxite; f, female tergite X; g, h, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351614/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Unfortunately, the legs of the 
<typeStatus box="[1237,1333,189,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">holotype</typeStatus>
are missing and therefore we are (except for the sexually dimorphic male tergite X) at present not able to find any significant characters to distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jäch &amp; Díaz &amp; Skale" authorityYear="2013" box="[1104,1288,286,310]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaelbalkei">
<emphasis box="[1104,1123,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1138,1288,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">michaelbalkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1341,1474,286,310]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manguao">
<emphasis box="[1341,1360,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1375,1474,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">manguao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally. Male tergite VIII apically distinctly produced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[835,1474,381,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
Male terminal sternite and spiculum (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1337,381,405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[113,148,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,197,2010]" captionTargetId="figure-8@7.[221,1352,177,2030]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 8. Hydraena michaelbalkei: a, aedeagus in lateral view; b, aedeagus, dorsal view; c, aedeagus, ventral view; d, male sternite X and spiculum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351608/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 8d</figureCitation>
): Somewhat resembling a contrabass, more elongate than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1342,1474,415,438]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manguao">
<emphasis box="[1342,1474,415,438]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. manguao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Freitag &amp; Jäch 2007: Fig. 25d); apex more widely rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[835,1475,541,854]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[956,1063,541,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[113,148,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,197,2010]" captionTargetId="figure-8@7.[221,1352,177,2030]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 8. Hydraena michaelbalkei: a, aedeagus in lateral view; b, aedeagus, dorsal view; c, aedeagus, ventral view; d, male sternite X and spiculum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351608/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 8a–c</figureCitation>
): In ventral and dorsal view distinctly Y-shaped as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1151,575,598]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manguao">
<emphasis box="[1013,1151,575,598]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. manguao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Freitag &amp; Jäch, 2007: Fig. 25a–c), 
<taxonomicName authority="Jach &amp; Diaz" authorityName="Jach &amp; Diaz" authorityYear="1999" box="[923,1192,605,630]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sautakei">
<emphasis box="[923,1047,607,630]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. sautakei</emphasis>
Jäch &amp; Díaz
</taxonomicName>
(Jäch &amp; Díaz, 1999: 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,171,2060,2082]" captionTargetBox="[166,1446,190,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-8@6.[43,1493,170,2020]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 7. Hydraena yangae: a, aedeagus in lateral view; b, aedeagus, dorsal view (setae of left paramere omitted in a, b); c, aedeagus, ventral view (setae of right paramere omitted); d, male sternite X and spiculum; e, gonocoxite; f, female tergite X; g, h, spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351606" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351606/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1959" box="[909,1045,639,662]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyatakei">
<emphasis box="[909,1045,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. miyatakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jäch &amp; Díaz, 1999: 
<figureCitation box="[1271,1335,637,661]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[113,148,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,197,2010]" captionTargetId="figure-8@7.[221,1352,177,2030]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 8. Hydraena michaelbalkei: a, aedeagus in lateral view; b, aedeagus, dorsal view; c, aedeagus, ventral view; d, male sternite X and spiculum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351608/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Main piece rather straight in lateral view; with only one short dorsal seta near base of distal lobe. Left paramere distinctly shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[862,994,735,758]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manguao">
<emphasis box="[862,994,735,758]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. manguao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distinctly thinner than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jach &amp; Diaz" authorityYear="1999" box="[1275,1396,735,758]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sautakei">
<emphasis box="[1275,1396,735,758]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. sautakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyatakei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. miyatakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with few apical setae; right paramere (as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jach &amp; Diaz" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sautakei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. sautakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1959" box="[977,1115,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyatakei">
<emphasis box="[977,1115,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">H. miyatakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) completely fused to main piece, mainly indicated by the presence of two groups of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[835,1474,893,1045]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Secondary sexual characters: Characters of male legs unknown. Male metaventral plaques thin and short (confined to basal half), carinate. Male tergite X with subapical, asymmetrically heart-shaped excavation; apex slightly excised, right corner longer than left one.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="65" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[835,1474,1084,1173]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,958,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Etymology.</emphasis>
— Named for Michael Balke (ZSM), excellent water beetle specialist, who collected the 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1371,1117,1141]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">holotype</typeStatus>
(together with Lars Hendrich).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[835,1473,1212,1269]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,992,1212,1237]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Distribution.</emphasis>
— So far known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1355,1473,1213,1237]" name="Singapore" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(MacRitchie Reservoir), see 
<figureCitation box="[1148,1228,1245,1269]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[137,172,2090,2112]" captionTargetBox="[137,1470,1208,2063]" captionTargetId="figure-8@14.[137,1478,1202,2067]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 15. Geographical map of Singapore, showing distribution of Hydraenidae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351618/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
